long_desc.thetext:
I often get the following meaningless error message:

Error in property sliceTop of class qx.ui.decoration.css3.BorderImage in method setSliceTop with incoming value 'null': Null value is not allowed!

"The reason for this error message is that a decoration image is missing."

The problem is that the error message generator by qooxdoo is meaningless,
because this error message occurs although I do not set a sliceTop-property directly.
I had already spent an hour to debug through the qooxdoo code to find the reason for this error.
The error message should rather look like this:
"The image guilibrary/ui/decoration/appDecoration-t.png could not be found."


A better error message could be generated by adding the lines "throw new Error..." to the class qx.ui.decoration.Grid:

qx.Class.define("qx.ui.decoration.Grid", 

 __setBorderImage : function(baseImage)
  ...
  var topSlice = ResourceManager.getImageHeight(prefix + "-t" + ext);

  var leftSlice = ResourceManager.getImageWidth(prefix + "-l" + ext);

  // Code added for better error messages
  if( ! topSlice ) 
    throw new Error("The image " + prefix + "-t" + ext + " was not found);
  if( ! leftSlice ) 
    throw new Error("The image " + prefix + "-l" + ext + " was not found);

  this.__impl.setSlice([topSlice, leftSlice]);
}
